name Gluten-Free Bread
serves 1 loaf
attrib https://theloopywhisk.com/2020/04/02/ultimate-gluten-free-bread/
desc Gluten-free bread with an open, moist crumb and a crispy crust.
note <p>Leave the loaf to cool completely before slicing - this is especially important
  with gluten-free bread, as the crumb sets during cooling. Slicing while slightly warm
  is acceptable, but not while hot.</p>
  <p>Keeps for 3-4 days in a cool, dry place wrapped in a tea towel. From day 3,
  toasting is recommended.</p>
tags bread, gluten free

# Preparation

- "fresh yeast"
- 20 g sugar
- 150 ml warm water
Mix the yeast, sugar and water and leave for 10-15 minutes until the mixture foams.
-> yeast

- 20 g psyllium husks
- 240 ml water
@nodep
Stir together and leave for 15-30 seconds until a gel forms.
-> psyllium gel

- 130 g buckwheat flour
- 100 g potato starch
- 90 g rice flour
- 10 g salt
@nodep
Combine the dry ingredients.
-> flour mixture

- 1 tbsp apple cider vinegar
= yeast
= psyllium gel
= flour mixture
<p>Add the yeast mixture, psyllium gel and vinegar to the flour mixture. Knead for
5-10 minutes until a smooth, homogeneous dough forms that pulls away from the sides of
the bowl. Shape into a ball, place in a lightly oiled bowl, cover with a damp tea towel
and leave to rise for 1 hour until doubled in size.</p>

<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C. Shape the dough into a loaf on a lightly oiled surface and
place in a rice flour-dusted proofing basket or a greased loaf tin. Score the top.</p>
<p>Bake at 220°C for 30-40 minutes until the crust is deep brown and the loaf sounds
hollow when tapped on the bottom. Leave to cool completely on a wire rack.</p>
